<div id="review_45439116" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/45439116" />
    <a title="Moira Russell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1630617-moira-russell"><img alt="Moira Russell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1256449807p2/1630617.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/45439116?book_show_action=true">Feb 05, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Moira Russell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Moira Russell" href="/user/show/1630617-moira-russell">Moira Russell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780385509510" href="/book/show/830716.Under_the_Banner_of_Heaven">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1630617-moira-russell?shelf=underwhelmed">underwhelmed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer45439116" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16454927854976564092">Somewhere, there is a story aching to be told about Mormonism, the positive and negative effects of religious faith on thought and psychological development, the painting of an integrated mainstream with the tarred brush of extremist fringes, and the general place of religion in US culture. This book is oh, so totally not it.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


